\subsection*{\IWBlangGerEng{Beschreibung}{Description}}%
% >>> CONTENTS OF FILE source/TUM/Styles/TUMbeamer_doc.tex: <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
% Documentation of file TUMbeamer.sty%
The \IWBdocumentationStyle{IWBbeamer} style creates a default style for presentations. It can be used for lectures, conference presentations or student thesis presentations. The style complies in general with the TUM corporate design, such that it can also be used for external presentations (e.\,g. conferences).\par%
%
To customize the colors, fonts, font sizes or even complete templates one can use the standard beamer macros%
\begin{itemize}%
  \item \IWBdocumentationCode{\textbackslash setbeamercolor\{template name\}\{<key=value> list\}},%
  \item \IWBdocumentationCode{\textbackslash setbeamerfont\{template name\}\{<key=value> list\}},%
  \item \IWBdocumentationCode{\textbackslash setbeamersize\{size name=<dim>\}},%
  \item \IWBdocumentationCode{\textbackslash setbeamertemplate\{template name\}\{your definition\}}.%
\end{itemize}%
%
There is a useful cheat-sheet on how to modify the style of your beamer presentation available online:\par%
\url{http://www.cpt.univ-mrs.fr/~masson/latex/Beamer-appearance-cheat-sheet.pdf}
%
%
%
% >>> CONTENTS OF FILE source/MW/IWB/Styles/IWBbeamer_doc.tex: <<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<<
% Documentation of file IWBbeamer.sty
%
%
%
%

% Documentation of file TUMdocumentation.sty%
The \IWBdocumentationStyle{IWBdocumentation} style is used to specify the layout of \textbf{this} document. There are several commands to typeset special names:%
%
\begin{center}%
    \begin{tabular}{|lll|}%
        \hline%
        \textbf{Command} & \textbf{Output} & \textbf{Description}\\\hline%
        \hyperref[sec:command_IWBdocumentationModule]{\textbackslash IWBdocumentationModule} & \IWBdocumentationModule{module} & typesets module names\\%
        \hyperref[sec:command_IWBdocumentationStyle]{\textbackslash IWBdocumentationStyle} & \IWBdocumentationStyle{style} & typesets style names\\%
        \hyperref[sec:command_IWBdocumentationTemplate]{\textbackslash IWBdocumentationTemplate} & \IWBdocumentationTemplate{template} & typesets template names\\%
        \hyperref[sec:command_IWBdocumentationOption]{\textbackslash IWBdocumentationOption} & \IWBdocumentationOption{option} & typesets options\\%
        \hyperref[sec:command_IWBdocumentationCode]{\textbackslash IWBdocumentationCode} & \IWBdocumentationCode{code} & typesets LaTeX code\\%
        \hline%
    \end{tabular}%
\end{center}%
